<paragraph blockId="37.[806,1421,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="38.[164,779,1361,1750]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="37" pageNumber="71">Head eyes present; rostrum subequal to lateral cephalic lobes. Antenna 1 stout, setose, longer than pereonites 1–6 together; article 2 slightly shorter than article 3; flagellum with two articles; flagellum article 1 with few aesthetascs; accessory flagellum absent. Gnathopod 1 propodus palm acute, serrate, and with short and long pappose setae; dactylus not reaching end of palm. Gnathopod 2 carpochelate; basis anterior margin slightly concave and smooth; carpus enlarged, with one large posterodistal process very produced forward, with a middle tooth; propodus 1.9 times as long as wide; propodus posterior margin straight; dactylus slightly shorter than propodus, with one marginal tooth. Pleopod 3 absent. Telson wider than long and weakly cleft.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301893" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5301893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301893/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="72" startId="38.[164,243,1244,1263]" targetBox="[386,1219,198,1214]" targetPageId="38">
