<subSubSection lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1441,1819,1903]" lastBlockId="41.[144,759,198,587]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[826,1035,1851,1872]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[826,1035,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">Notopoma teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1042,1127,1851,1872]" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry &amp; Berents, 1996" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[1312,1441,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">N. africana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry JK &amp; Berents PB" box="[826,1118,1881,1903]" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" pagination="75 - 109" refId="ref31067" refString="Lowry JK, Berents PB. 1996. The Ericthonius group, a new perspective on an old problem (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea). Records of the Australian Museum 48: 75 - 109." type="journal article" year="1996">Lowry &amp; Berents, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lowry, 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallohidea">
<emphasis box="[1192,1340,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">N. fallohidea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry JK" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" pagination="183 - 211" refId="ref31036" refString="Lowry JK. 1981. The amphipod genus Cerapus in New Zealand and subantarctic waters (Corophioidea, Ischyroceridae). Journal of Natural History 15: 183 - 211." type="journal article" year="1981">Lowry, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the long thin antennae, about half the body length, and the dactylus of gnathopod 2 more than half the propodus length. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" box="[629,759,259,281]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[629,759,259,281]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a slender palp of the mandible and seven robust setae on the outer plate of maxilla 1; however, 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[144,254,351,372]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[144,254,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[262,346,351,372]" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from both species by the 2-articulate flagellum of antenna 1, the distoventral process of gnathopod 2 more produced anteriorly, and a more inflated propodus. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[144,254,474,495]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[144,254,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[262,346,474,495]" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" box="[489,619,473,495]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[489,619,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of eyes, absence of pleopod 3, the inner ramus of uropod 3 about two-thirds the outer ramus length, and the telson weakly cleft.
</paragraph>
